CONTRIBUTING.md
     1→Contributing
     4→All the contributions are welcome! Please open [an
     5→issue](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/new) or send us
     6→a pull request.
     7→
     8→Executing the tests:
     9→
    10→    $ uv venv
    11→    $ uv pip install -r requirements.txt
    12→    $ uv pip install -e .
    13→    $ uv ruff check .
    14→    $ uv format .
    15→    $ uv run pytest
    16→
    17→or with [tox](https://pypi.org/project/tox/) installed:
    18→
    19→    $ tox
    20→
    21→
    22→Use of pre-commit is recommended:
    23→
    24→    $ uv run precommit install
    25→
    26→
    27→Documentation is published with [mkdocs]():
    28→
    29→```shell
    30→$ uv pip install -r requirements-docs.txt
    31→$ uv pip install -e .
    32→$ uv run mkdocs serve
    33→```
    34→
    35→Open http://127.0.0.1:8000/ to view the documentation locally.
